name: The Retro Lab 5s
description: tomorrow marks the release of the Air Jordan 5 “3Lab5″, that first pair in the new “Air Jordan Elements” line. The pair links up a couple of Jordan from Mike’s earlier days with Nike, bringing the iconic elephant print from the Air Jordan 3 over to the Air Jordan 5. Equally interesting is the premium packaging, which spells out the intent of the Elements line with some cool inserted materials.

name: The Bel Air 5s
description:
Named the Air Jordan 5 “Bel-Air”, the kicks find inspiration in the always colorful Will Smith on the Fresh Prince of Bel Air. Smith was known for his  dope kicks, flashy clothing, and reversed Bel Air Academy blazer. These kicks personify that character to a T.

The kicks feature Jordan’s coveted cool grey throughout the upper. And that’s as mundane as it gets. The sole is a striking court purple. Pink and lime green poop off as accents on the shoe, coloring the fire on the sole, stitched 23 number, and Jordan logos. Another extremely bright spot is the lining which is composed of a bright colorful print lining.

name: KD VI – PB & J
description:
Kevin Durant’s nostalgic childhood snack served as the basis for this colorway, which bounces a vibrant peanut butter tone off of jelly swoosh and accents. It’s peanut butter jelly time.

    Exclusive, textured jelly swoosh.
    The edge of a performance-based shoe with the style of a fresh kick.
    Solid rubber outsole provides durable traction.

name: Air Jordan 9 “Silver Anniversary NEVERWORN
description: The run of 25th Anniversary Air Jordans continues today with this Retro 9, ringing in the new year in celebratory fashion. We of course saw this shoe as a part of the complete collection, but this is the first time we’re getting a look at what could prove to be a 2010 release.

name: KD VI - Texas Nights
description:
he KD VI Men's Basketball Shoe was built with a new, responsive Nike Zoom unit, a more supportive upper and a lower-cut silhouette for better flex through the ankle-resulting in KD's lightest shoe to date.

    Visible Max Air in the heel for maximum impact protection on hard landings, plus a Nike Zoom unit in the forefoot for lightweight, low-profile responsiveness. Together with a Phylon midsole, they provide exceptional cushioning for every position on the court.
    The shoe's two-layer upper is ultra-thin and features Flywire technology-super-light, super-strong nylon cables that support the foot by encasing it in a secure hug. High-wrapped rubber at the outsole adds stability and support during quick cuts.
    A multidirectional outsole pattern offers excellent traction and durability for total control, with layers of rubber stripped away in some areas to maintain the shoe's light weight.
    The collar of the KD VI is lower than that of its predecessor, allowing more flexibility through the ankle.

name: Nike Air Max 95 No Sew- Grey & Blue
description:
Overview
Reviews
Customer liked...

STREAMLINED LOOK AND FEEL 



The Nike Air Max 95 No-Sew Men's Shoe features a Max Air unit and tough ripstop construction in the upper for lightweight cushioning and durability. No-sew tape in contrast colors provides an updated look while minimizing bulk in this reimagined version of a running original. 


Benefits 
•Ripstop material in the upper for durability and a lightweight fit 
•No-sew tape creates stair-stepped design for iconic style 
•Full-length polyurethane midsole for durability, stability and cushioning 
•Max Air units for lightweight cushioning and impact protection 
•Rubber Waffle outsole for traction and durability 
•Flex grooves for natural range of motion and flexibility 


Nike Air Max Origins 

Nike's revolutionary Air-Sole unit made its way into Nike footwear in the late '70s. In 1987, the Nike Air Max debuted with visible air in its heel, allowing fans more than just the feel of Air-Sole comfort. Suddenly they could see it. And just a few years later, the next-generation Nike Air Max 90 became a hit with both athletes and collectors by offering striking color combinations, lightweight performance and a cushioned ride.

name: Air Jordan IV (4)
description: This is the Air Jordan IV (4) "Toro" also referred to as the "Fire Red Nubuck" edition which is a new color way for 2013. The all red suede upper has become very popular since the Raging Bulls pack originally released. We've had recent releases which included an all red suede Spizike, AJ IX (9) Motorboat Jones, and even the Ewing 33 Hi came in a popular all red suede color way. For 2013 JB is bringing us this Air Jordan IV (4) model coming in an all fire red nubuck upper with black, cement grey and white accents. A very similar pair was previewed by Carmelo Anthony in 2012 and quickly became one of the more anticipated releases of the year. The Toro 4s are a beautiful Bulls colored model and make a perfect addition to any AJ collection.

name: The Oreo 5s
description: Of the many brand new Air Jordan 5 colorways that have arrived in 2013, it appears that this one is the sole pair without a clear theme attached. Previous versions included the touching “Doernbecher”, the “Black Grape” flipping a classic colorway, and the “Fear” that was connected to an old MJ ad campaign. As far as we can tell this Air Jordan 5 “Oreo” is without any backstory: it’s just a clean combo of black, cool grey, and white.

name: Air Jordan 5 GS PRE-ORDER 100% GUAREENTEED THE SIZE YOU PURCHASE
description: If you can fit into GS Jordans, there’s pretty much a guarantee that you’ll have access to colorful pairs year round. Proving that yet again is the Air Jordan 5, which is this time outfitted with a combination of tropical teal, club pink, and purple. Were the shoe to have come out a couple years prior we have a feeling there would be many cries of “South Beach” down in the comments, but fortunately people have moved on from associating every pair of that sort with that theme.

name: Laney Retro 5s
description: The retro pair of Jordans is one of those rare ones that plays with the lacing a little bit-they’re outfitted with the same rounded off laces that the shoes sported back during their 2000 debut. The colorway looks to be the last of the Air Jordan 5s in 2013 that we’ve ever seen before

name: Military retro 4s
description:
Jordan Brand has clearly made the Retro IV and Retro XII focal points of the first half of 2012. Today, June 9, will be the third adult Retro IV release of the year when the “Military Blue” colorway hits stores. With all the hype this weekend surrounding the release of a certain other shoe, this Jordan release has seemed to slip under the radar. A mostly white upper is aided by military blue accents on the heel, lace tabs, tongue and midsole. Neutral grey is found on the nubuck toe wrap, ankle supports, and outsole. The IV is a classic no matter what colorway it is in but the simplicity of this release with the blue accents makes this one stand out. This will be the first time the white/neutral grey/military blue retro IV will be released since 2012.

The Jordan Retro IV “Military Blue” releases today, June 9, and can be found at Foot Locker, House of Hoops by Foot Locker, and Footlocker.com for $160. A link to buy online can be found below. Kids sizes will also be available for this release.

name: Photo Blue Retro 9
description: The shoe’s upper consists of black leather, as well as matching black nubuck that utilizes specks throughout. Meanwhile photo blue accents are seen on the stitching, lace loops, and lining. Finishing off the look is a classic white midsole.

name: CAMO Army Foamposites SIZE 10
description: In 1997, basketball shoe designer Eric Avar crafted a shoe that would forever set the standards for sneaker innovation. This Nike Air Foamposite Pro Premium delivers the legendary looks with a army camo print. The upper design is complimented by electric yellow accents and a gum rubber outsole that works with a carbon fiber plate to provide bold style and long-lasting wear.

name: Nike Air Force Ones
description: Sometimes you just have to appreciate a complete classic and that is exactly what we have here with an upcoming release this month in the form of the Nike Air Force 1 Low “White/Gum”. The Nike sneaker sports a classic White leather construction but adds in a smooth Gum sole that we don’t see too often. The Nike Air Force 1 Low “White/Gum” will be dropping in select Nike Sportswear accounts so stay tuned for complete information

name: Gamma Blue Lebron 11s
description: The "Gamma Blue" Nike LeBron 11 has been another heavily discussed upcoming Fall 2013 Nike Basketball release. After several updated looks at the design, Nike officially unveils the colorway and above is the official imagery. The concept of this specific colorway stems from tempered steel which is turned into a blue shade when heated at a high level, much like LeBron's game.

name: Fire Red 5s
description:
2013 RETRO 5 fire reds

Full-grain leather and Durabuk upper for a premium look and feel
Nike Air units in the heel and forefoot for plush cushioning
Clear rubber outsole with herringbone pattern for traction
Inner sleeve for a snug, comfortable fit
Flex grooves at the outsole for enhanced flexibility

Since his game-winning shot that brought the National Championship to North Carolina, Michael Jordan has been at the forefront of basketball consciousness. He took the court in 1985 wearing the original Air Jordan I, setting a new standard for performance and style, simultaneously breaking league rules and his opponents' will while capturing the imagination of fans worldwide. Ever evolving, ever at the pinnacle of imagination, the Air Jordan line is the ultimate in basketball footwear

name: Retro 11s Gamma Blues Pre Order
description:
This holiday seasons most anticipated release is almost here, The Air Jordan 11 “Gamma Blue” has been on everyone’s wish list since they were officially announced to release.  The Air Jordan 11 has always been a big deal to sneakerheads around Christmas time. Usually Jordan Brand release a retro of the Air Jordan 11 silhouette, but this time we have a never before seen version of the sneaker.

The new colorway features a predominantly Black upper with accents of Gamma Blue and Yellow which leads people to believe it might be a “Laney” inspired colorway.  A Blue tinted translucent sole finishes off the sneaker look adding to the subtle design.  Set to release December 21st, I’m sure we’re all hoping for an early Christmas
